t nominee companies or trusts</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Land should be taxed as a business.</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Purchase by communities and tenants should be encouraged</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Single farm payments should only be made to named individuals and only one to any individual.</span></li><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Subsidies should be phased out and converted to grants encouraging new land usage not paying for past or historic use which is no longer viable.</span></li></ul><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">1</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How does Scotland compare to other countries in terms of the pattern of land ownership?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">For vast areas of Scotland it is unknown who the actual owners are.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Registration is allowed for nominee companies, trusts and consortia with no reference to those financing them.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There should be a register of land ownership for Scotland with no exclusions.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Communities and individuals have found it difficult if not impossible to determine ownership in some cases where a development might be proposed. This is wrong.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Without the knowledge of who owns and benefits from the land it is possible that criminal activity could be supported and even subsidies paid to criminals who invest in land.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Crown </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Commissioners</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> should be consistent and take action against all who attempt fraud such as selling half of the </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Cuillins</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> when they don’t own it. The land register should show this definitively.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Reading of Andy Wightman’s book ‘The poor had no lawyers’ should be compulsory. Perhaps a chapter at a time to allow anger to subside.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What are the benefits and disadvantages of the current pattern of land ownership, and to what extent is this pattern sustained and reinforced by subsidy and taxation arrangements</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Land ownership applies a secondary planning policy on any tenants of that land. If the owner disagrees then it will not happen. There is no incentive or provision for tenants to benefit from improvements on land</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Single Farm Payment Schemes should be just that. Any owner should not be entitled to more than one. </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Large estates with multiple tenanted farms should be classified as one farm unless they are sold to separate farmers. This is a subsidy which is not reaching those who it is intended for.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Large estates argue that they are businesses due to a minority affording to hunt and fish on them. They should therefore pay business rates. In fact they employ few people and then only seasonally.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Balmoral</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> Estate should not be subject to a separate legislation avoiding tax.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Money laundering for criminals is almost encouraged – what better way to hide funds when ownership is hidden?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Is the current system of land tenure in Scotland the most efficient model for food security?</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">In particular, is the current land ownership pattern contributing to, or inhibiting, economic and community development? Is it socially just?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Land buy-outs by communities show how they feel to have an ‘unjust’ landlord.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Knoydart</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Eigg</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> and Rum show this and are thriving communities.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Large areas of land are at the whim of an absentee landlord.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Given mounting political interest in, or commitment to, a programme of land reform in Scotland, what form should this programme take?</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Named ownership for a start.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The community right to buy should be extended.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Schemes to allow ownership to transfer without coming onto the market should be curtailed, except perhaps inheritance.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Perhaps it is asking too much for political parties to follow through on their pre-election rhetoric.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Properties which is not being managed or intentionally left to become derelict should be taxed additionally. The land value is often being inflated due to a derelict building circumventing planning rules. It is criminal to see so many houses being left to rot rather than sold or renovated at the same time as a housing demand.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What sort of subsidies and grants are available to landed estate owners in Scotland? What are the advantages and disadvantages of the subsidy regime? In particular, are support payments being capitalized into land values and making these higher than they otherwise would be?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Rental for </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">windfarms</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> is an incredible amount compared to that </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">payed</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> to the local communities</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Single farm payments should mean that. Only a single payment for only one farm to any owner.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">SRDP grants are set up to benefit large landowners and are extremely difficult for community groups to access. They do not recognise the need or pathway to accommodate them.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Any public subsidy should bring with it some public ownership. The poor are being fleeced to subsidise the rich in many cases.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Why do we pay some subsidies when there is no market for what we </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">subsidi</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">se</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">?. If people don’t want to buy wool or beef then the market should decide. How long do we support a non sustainable industry? Do we continue to pay unemployed bobbin makers or crinoline designers? There are alternative uses for land.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">If sheep don’t pay then perhaps timber will. Break the vicious circle and pay to diversify not continue a dead industry. If an industry is failing then public funds are used to retrain the staff not pay them indefinitely.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How does the tax regime affect the way in which land is owned in Scotland? For instance, does it offer landed estate owners the opportunity to minimize the tax they pay, thereby increasing the value </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">of land, adding to speculative interest (on the part of those looking for ways to minimize or avoid tax) and making it less likely that it will be made available to others?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Of course it does. You don’t even know who owns the land, yet alone where they are domiciled or pay tax.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Investors make money from the land not the property or improvements on it.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It cost</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> the same to build a house on two different plots but the purchase cost differs due to the land value. Hence the land value should be taxed.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Reference ‘</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">The poor had no lawyers’</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">7</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How easy is it for communities in Scotland to take ownership of land and other assets? Should it be made easier in the light of the substantial achievements of existing community ownership groups?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It is not easy. For instance why were the crafting counties in the North East excluded from crafting legislation?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">SRDP grants are extremely difficult for community groups to access.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">They seem to be set up to maintain the status quo and subsidise large estates. There is no great profit or turn over for some of these groups so they seem inconsequential as they obviously have no value.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Why is it impossible for publicly owned land held by the Forestry Commission to be handed over to Community ownership? It seems that the state insists it is bought by grants from the like of the lottery fund hence filling the state coffers from the lottery. This is immoral and not what the lottery is for.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">8</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How easy is it for tenant farmers in Scotland to buy their farms? Should they be granted an absolute right to buy? Would such a right be compatible with human rights conventions and declarations?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Yes, it will increase the population’s investment in the land.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">9</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Is there a case for establishing a Land Agency to facilitate both the expansion of community ownership and the creation of new, especially “starter”, tenancies on land acquired for this purpose?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Yes!</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It should also encompass all Crown Estates, SNH and Local Authority held land.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">10</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How easy is it for land in public ownership to be transferred to communities and other private individuals, where that would be in the public interest? Should steps be taken to make it easier? For instance, should the UK and Scottish Governments compile a register showing land and assets for disposal? Should there be changes in the way in which such land and assets are valued? What UK Treasury rules are relevant to this area?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">It is too complex – Community groups are expected to buy the land from the</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Forestry Commission often through grants such as the National lottery. The public buying from the public.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">There should be a register of all public land and common land</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">11</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Should a Land Value Tax of some sort be introduced in Scotland, as a replacement or addition to council tax and business rates?</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">YES.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">House prices vary by the area and land value independently of the actual house built on them.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">The house is an improvement to the land and is to be encouraged not always taxed.</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">Land used as a business such as a sporting estate should be taxed as a business.</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p></div></body></html>